The Website violates www.imortgagecentral.com rights in several different ways: 1) Your clients copying and distribution of the ENTIRE Website listed at e-loanweb.com , or any part of the Website, is copyright infringement against our web property badcreditalliance.com under United States = Copyright law. As we are sure you are aware, Federal law, specifically Section = 106 of the Copyright Act (17 U.S.C. =A7 106) gives www.imortgagecentral.com = exclusive right to reproduce and distribute the Website. Under Federal law, a plaintiff may not only enjoin the unlawful infringement of its Work, but = may also obtain damages, including, but not limited to, the defendant's = profits and any damages sustained by the plaintiff. A plaintiff may elect to receive statutory damages up to $100,000 if the court finds that = defendant willfully infringed the copyright. Moreover, a court may award a = successful plaintiff reasonable attorney fees. 2) Compare Choose and Save (U.S. Reg. No. 78766491; http://tess2.uspto.gov/bin/showfield?f=3Ddoc &state=3Dqf24hi.2.1) and IMORTGAGE CENTRAL (U.S. Reg. No. 3168212; http://tess2.uspto.gov/bin/showfield?f=3Ddoc &state=3D92r93l.2.1) are registered trademarks of our company, Loan = Alliance Inc. Our federal registration of this trademark provides us with certain proprietary rights. This includes the right to restrict the use of the trademark, or a confusingly similar trademark, in association with confusingly similar products or services. It is important that we = exercise our right to protect our trademark. It serves as an important and distinctive representation of the origin of our products as well as the goodwill of our company. State and federal law supports our position = that confusingly similar trademarks may cause confusion among customers. This confusion may cause substantial harm to the trademark by facilitating = the loss of its effectiveness in establishing a distinct association between = it, our products and services, and our company's goodwill. Moreover, a court = may award a successful plaintiff reasonable attorney fees. =20 =20 We hereby demand the following pursuant to the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (the =93DMCA=94): 1. Your company immediately cause the Work to be removed from the http://www. e-loanweb.com website and any other website to which your = client distributed the Work; 2. Your company immediately cease and desist from your client = making any further distribution and use of the Work; 3. A complete list of publications to which your client distributed = the Work; 4. Loan Alliance Inc. swears, under penalty of perjury, that the information in the notification is accurate and that our company is the copyright owner that is infringed. =20 Please respond by letter indicating your intention to cease & desist = your client=92s illegal use of our trademarks or any confusingly similar = trademark through your network, and our DMCA demand, within five (5) calendar = days. =20 =20 =20 We look forward to receiving your timely response. = Dear ehostpros.com,

Loan Alliance Inc. has recently = discovered that the operator(s) of http://www.e-loanweb.com (the “Website”) IS ONCE AGAIN blatantly violating our web property www.imortgagecentral.com intellectual property rights. Loan Alliance Inc. provides this = notification of infringement pursuant to the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (the “DMCA”). The Website = violates www.imortgagecentral.com = rights in several different ways:

1) Your clients copying and distribution of the = ENTIRE Website listed = at e-loanweb.com = , or any part of the Website, is copyright infringement against our web property badcreditalliance.com under United States Copyright = law.  As we are sure you are aware, Federal law, specifically Section 106 of = the Copyright Act (17 U.S.C. =A7 106) gives www.imortgagecentral.com exclusive right to reproduce and = distribute the Website.  Under Federal law, a plaintiff may not only enjoin = the unlawful infringement of its Work, but may also obtain damages, = including, but not limited to, the defendant's profits and any damages sustained by the plaintiff.  A plaintiff may elect to receive statutory damages up to $100,000 if the = court finds that defendant willfully infringed the copyright.  Moreover, a = court may award a successful plaintiff reasonable attorney = fees.

 2) Compare Choose and Save = (U.S. Reg. No. 78766491; http://tess2.uspto.gov/bin/showfield?f=3Ddoc&state=3Dqf24hi.2.1 <= /a>) and IMORTGAGE CENTRAL (U.S. Reg. = No. 3168212; http://tess2.uspto.gov/bin/showfield?f=3Ddoc&state=3D92r93l.2.1 <= /a>) = are registered trademarks = of our company, Loan Alliance = Inc. Our federal registration of this trademark provides us with certain = proprietary rights. This includes the right to restrict the use of the trademark, or = a confusingly similar trademark, in association with confusingly similar = products or services. It is important that we exercise our right to protect our trademark. It serves as an important and distinctive representation of = the origin of our products as well as the goodwill of our company. State and federal law supports our position that confusingly similar trademarks = may cause confusion among customers. This = confusion may cause substantial harm to the trademark by facilitating the loss of its effectiveness in establishing a distinct association between it, our = products and services, and our company's goodwill. Moreover, a court = may award a successful plaintiff reasonable attorney = fees.

 

 

   We hereby demand the following pursuant to = the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (the = “DMCA”):

1.      Your company = immediately cause the Work to be removed from the = http://www. = e-loanweb.com website and any other website to which your client distributed the = Work;

2.      Your company = immediately cease and desist from your client making any further distribution and = use of the Work;

3.      A complete = list of publications to which your client distributed the = Work;

4.      A description of what measures you have taken, or are = going to take, to insure that the publications will comply with our request to = cease distributing the Work through your = network;

5.      = Loan Alliance Inc. has a good faith belief = that use of the copyrighted materials described above on the infringing web pages = was not authorized by Loan Alliance Inc., its agent, or the = law.

6.      Loan Alliance Inc. swears, under penalty of perjury, that the = information in the notification is accurate and that our company is the copyright = owner that is infringed.

 

Please respond by letter indicating your intention to cease & = desist your client’s illegal = use of our trademarks = or any confusingly similar = trademark through your network, and our DMCA demand, within five (5) calendar = days.

 

 

 

We look forward to receiving your timely response.

Regards,

Legal Affairs

Loan Alliance Inc.
Phone: 615.599.9609 x705
